race.comment: The $200,000 Listed Phelan Ready for the babies. ITCHINTOGO (1) was well supported on debut but just ran into one better here on that occasion. Maloney sticks in the saddle following that first-up placing and will have derived benefit from that day at the races. Can feature with natural improvement. BOLLENTE BELLA (12) looked handy winning a recent Gosford trial and is sure to be well-educated out of the Kris Lees barn. Maps well from gate three and should be kept very safe. The well-bred SNITSKA (6) (dam was a Group 2 winner) has shown ability at the trials and must be respected out of the Waller yard. Can run a race on debut. ELUSIVE CAPITAL (9) managed to place at the Sunny Coast when facing the starter for the first time and will have come on with that run now under the belt. In the mix. ACRODANCE (11) is a first-up winner who should be underestimated.
